  <static seed="276" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/FractionSubtractionWordProblems50.pg">
    <statement><p>Ken and Nenia are sharing a pizza. Ken ate <m>{{\frac{1}{8}}}</m> of the pizza, and Nenia ate <m>{{\frac{1}{9}}}</m> of the pizza. How much more pizza did Ken eat than Nenia?</p>
<p>Ken ate <fillin characters="10" name="AnSwEr0001"/> more of the pizza than Nenia ate.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{1}{72}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To find the difference of two numbers, we use subtraction:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {{\frac{1}{8}}} - {{\frac{1}{9}}} 
      \amp = \frac{1 \cdot 9}{8 \cdot 9}-\frac{1 \cdot 8}{9 \cdot 8} \\
      \amp = \frac{9}{72} - \frac{8}{72} \\
      \amp = \frac{9-8}{72} \\
      
      \amp = {{\frac{1}{72}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Ken ate <m>{{\frac{1}{72}}}</m> more of the pizza than Nenia ate.</p>
</solution>
